Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] Only my father\Nwould turn a hostile takeover
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.00,0:01:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,into a fluffy PR move.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.37,0:01:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- On the news, he said he\Njust wanted to break bread
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.58,0:01:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and hash things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.08,0:01:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it won't be so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.67,0:01:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We do want the General to start opening up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.62,0:01:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to these people, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.04,0:01:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, but on his terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.87,0:01:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ironwood's going to be locked in a room
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.54,0:02:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,at his rival's own dinner party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.42,0:02:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jacques says\Nhe's happy to moderate,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.42,0:02:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but all that really means is he'll
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.87,0:02:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,be the one controlling the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.00,0:02:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Not hard to imagine how\Nthat's gonna play out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.12,0:02:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] I still can't believe he won.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.75,0:02:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Robyn was supposed to be\Nthe people's champion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.00,0:02:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't she? (sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.46,0:02:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just too many coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.87,0:02:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- You really think your\Ndad might have something
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with Salem?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I think my father would\Ndo whatever it takes to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.62,0:02:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- And we should do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.50,0:02:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Meaning...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, no one knows\Nyour dad better than you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of everyone going tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say you're the only\None who could snoop
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.29,0:02:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,around the house and not be questioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.79,0:02:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jacques Schnee is up to something,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.46,0:02:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.92,0:03:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Suppose we should smile for the cameras?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sir, with all due respect,\Nyou'd have to pay me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.79,0:03:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good evening, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.83,0:03:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where's Klein?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.96,0:03:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- What an interesting way to\Nsay, "Hello, dear brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.92,0:03:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"how have you been?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.79,0:03:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid you won't find him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.67,0:03:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He was let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.37,0:03:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine why.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.04,0:03:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,General, exactly how large do you think
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.21,0:03:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,our dining room table is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.08,0:03:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- I happen to know it's enormous,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.04,0:03:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but most of my guests will be on standby
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.75,0:03:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in case the Council requests\Nadditional eye witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, I'm sure they'll\Nbe happily celebrating
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,your father's victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.08,0:04:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- For those of you joining\Nus in the dining room,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.21,0:04:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,please follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.42,0:04:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wish us luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- (chuckling) I mean,\Nthey already invited you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.08,0:04:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't they?\N(chuckling)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.67,0:04:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Care for a drink, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh, no, no thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.37,0:04:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think ill just stick\Nto patrolling the grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.92,0:04:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Words out of my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.12,0:04:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right, well, don't wander off,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,don't break anything, and be ready
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.92,0:04:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in case the General calls on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.46,0:04:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Vine] Hors d'oeuvres?\N- [Elm] Let's eat them out of house and home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.96,0:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Counterpoint, how\Nabout we do wander off,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.54,0:04:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,consider breaking things, and\Nthen all that other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll be in touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dear sister, I was hoping\Nwe could use this time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.83,0:04:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.62,0:05:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh...\N- I have to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.42,0:05:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,why did you go through so much trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.08,0:05:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave home, only to come crawling back?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.92,0:05:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- This might be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.46,0:05:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] General Ironwood,\Nplease: have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.21,0:05:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Councilman Sleet, Councilwoman Camilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.62,0:05:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Robyn] Councilwoman Hill would\Nhave had a nice ring to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.08,0:05:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I suppose I should just be grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.29,0:05:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I got invited to the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- Miss Hill, that vigor\Nof yours is precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.04,0:05:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,why we're grateful to\Nhave you with us tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is she doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.79,0:05:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- What we're all doing here, James,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,addressing the concerns of our kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.46,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which means we have much to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:05:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] Indeed. I was\Nhoping we could start by --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:06:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] Are we safe\Nwith her here, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I do recall come confusion regarding
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,her involvement in that horrific massacre.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- As the official report stated,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that footage was doctored.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Penny is completely under my control.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] Which is concerning, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.75,0:06:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Concerning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.92,0:06:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] Let's talk about\Nexactly what it is you control.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why won't this kid buzz off?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- We need to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- What was that earlier\Nabout breaking things?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] Well, Whitley, I'm sure the company
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.42,0:06:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is lucky to have you,\Nbut if you'll pardon me--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- And where exactly is\Nit that you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.33,0:06:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] Careful, messy\Nfood comin' through!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.92,0:06:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Whitley] Of course, once I'm\Nold enough to drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.50,0:06:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the company has promised\Nme my own parking space,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.62,0:06:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Butler] Care for a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.79,0:06:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't mind if I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.04,0:07:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,(crashing)\N- [Nora] Oh no, look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm going to go get some hors d'oeuvres.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.71,0:07:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,(splashing)\NOops.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.42,0:07:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- If you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.58,0:07:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- The fact of the matter\Nis, you've operated
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with a fair amount of autonomy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.08,0:07:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for the past few years, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we need now is for you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.54,0:07:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to work with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] Sir, I have--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's obvious that no kingdom intends
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.21,0:07:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to declare war on Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:07:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We had no involvement in\Nthe incident at Haven,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we have proof our drones weren't\Nacting on orders at Beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, the\Nclosure of Atlas borders
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.42,0:08:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is only serving to hurt our relations
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.04,0:08:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- I--\N- The rest of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hurting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.25,0:08:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The people of Atlas are suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.75,0:08:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they want to know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.71,0:08:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] Quite right, Ms. Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm afraid there's\Nmore than just your choices
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.54,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that have brought harm to\Nour citizens as of late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.62,0:08:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Have your forces found\Nany additional evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.62,0:08:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as to who is slaughtering\Ninnocent civilians down in Mantle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.75,0:08:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- That is an ongoing investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.17,0:08:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the details of which are\Nclassified, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.54,0:08:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] I'm afraid\Nof the ever-growing list
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of classified information\Nyou seem to be keeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked our fellow councilmen here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to shed some light on your\NAmity Colosseum project
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and, as it turns out, they\Nknow about as much as I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Even you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.42,0:08:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] The Amity\Nproject will help with all
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the issues you've\Npresented, but you have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.21,0:08:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand that discretion\Nis a top priority
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.50,0:09:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jacques] Are you\Nsaying you don't trust us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.12,0:09:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- You can't just buy trust\Nlike everything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.83,0:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to earn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.87,0:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- I couldn't have said it better myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,General, if I may be blunt, you have spent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.17,0:09:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what little trust this\Ncouncil had left in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The hacker who turned\NAtlas drones against us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.67,0:09:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was never captured,\Nwhoever's been murdering
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,your critics is still at large.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we supposed to give you our trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.08,0:09:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when you've given us nothing as of late?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.62,0:09:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's not what--\N- Winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.33,0:09:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Winter] Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.54,0:10:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- Miss Schnee, is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.08,0:10:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm fine, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.33,0:10:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the great work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.04,0:10:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Willow] Hello darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.79,0:10:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Penny] Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.33,0:10:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll be fine, I just let my emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,get the better of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.92,0:10:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.00,0:10:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- You wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.04,0:10:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.00,0:10:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, no, what I mean is: this place
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,holds a lot of memories\Nfor me, specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.75,0:10:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was in\Ncontrol, but you heard me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I sounded like a petulant child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.87,0:10:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought you sounded fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.58,0:10:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You were just speaking from your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.54,0:10:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- And that is precisely the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have just stayed in line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.75,0:11:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- I guess you're right,\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.04,0:11:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry I couldn't\Ncome down for your party,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.54,0:11:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I'm not feeling well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.17,0:11:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Um, it's okay, Mom, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.83,0:11:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing in\Nyour father's office?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just looking for something I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.83,0:11:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's right, you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.21,0:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- I need to use father's computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.08,0:11:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why?\N- Because I think
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:11:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he may have done\Nsomething. Something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.33,0:12:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought we all simply\Nassumed that at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.08,0:12:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, well, some of us are trying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.58,0:12:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- He started locking his home computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.42,0:12:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But, he still has blind spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.54,0:12:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- You put a camera in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.25,0:12:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- I put them in every room of this house,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.92,0:12:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for our safety, in case\NI ever needed to...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.67,0:12:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't come back to stay, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.96,0:12:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:13:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,(sniffling) A man came by.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.37,0:13:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid your father may be involved
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in something more\Ndangerous than he realizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.50,0:13:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[Willow] No matter what happens, Weiss,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.87,0:13:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,please don't forget about your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.67,0:13:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] Whitley wants\Nnothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.92,0:13:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Willow] Of course not, you\Nleft him alone. With us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.46,0:13:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey mom, it's snowing!
